messages.message:
Hi Team, Can I get help in fixing the failing cypress.
Cypress is failing for this PR:-https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/61373 and I am unsure what is required in test cases to fix these errors.
Context: We have updated the logic to read the supported file extension list in FE. We have removed the hard-code list and added logic to read it from the environment. variable.

FYI, I have tested build and converse locally and it's working as expected.
Last Cypress run:- https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/13244/errors

hmm i can’t find the `pr-61373-cypress` sandbox in Crafting, did you delete it?

it seems there were a lot of 500 errors in the Cypress run for just loading frontend pages via `apps-server` , but i can’t see the `apps-server` logs since the `pr-61373-cypress` sandbox no longer exists in Crafting :disappointed:

for future reference, Cypress CI often has issues for old PRs (older than ~1 week)

either you need to delete the Crafting sandbox to re-create it since it doesn’t restart from hibernation correctly, or the licenses for the automatically created commercial/enterprise users expire
the PR itself looks good to me, so if you’re still having trouble with Cypress CI, you could ask an EM to force merge
